[SN]TITLE[SN]
Father and son deny Scarborough man's murder

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A father and son have pleaded not guilty to murdering a man in Scarborough.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Shaun Atkinson, 49, was found dead at a house in St John's Avenue in the North Yorkshire town on 27 December.
Barry Rewcroft, 51, and Ruben Rewcroft, 20, both of Raincliffe Avenue, Scarborough, denied the charge during a hearing at Leeds Crown Court.
Both men were remanded in custody and they will appear again before the same court on 19 June.
